inn1.comm: ripper first up, angled in back of a length, starts curling away just before pitching and jags past the outside edge
short of a length, not as short as the previous one, angled in, defended from the crease

terrific stuff from Anderson, and he needs three balls to strike, excellent delivery again, short of a length, bouncing and straightening just outside off, Finch is hopping as he prods from the crease and the ball carries nicely to first slip
all the movement from the batsman this time, walks outside off to a back of a length ball slanted in to middle, nudges it square
good length ball on the pad to the left hander who quietly plays it out to midwicket
middle stump line from a length, some extra bounce, he shuffles and taps it to leg
eases a pitched up delivery to the covers where it is not stopped cleanly allowing them to a single
short of a length ball on the stumps, pushed down the track
lifter, Warner opens up, gets on his toes and brings it down on to the pitch
a thick outside edge behind square on off as Warner plays back to a good length ball this time
holding the line outside off stump, he moves across and defends it solidly
he walks across, Woakes slants it in to middle and leg and Smith whips it square in the air, Broad drags it back with a slide near the rope, but they have run four anyway
short of a good length, middle and leg, Warner carefully taps it to on side, close to the pitch
a pitched up delivery, Warner is not really flowing forward, but he leans the upper body into it and finds the gap at cover
that was close, Warner went reaching forward this time, and pushed on the up, it went on the bounce to cover
sees it zipping across on the angle and lets it be
slight away shape taking it further away on the angle, and Warner leaves after having a look at it
swinging in now from Anderson, but into the pad, and Warner puts it away fine
had plenty of width on this one, it moved further away after pitching short of a length and sent it racing behind point with a cut off his toes
angled in now towards middle, Smith does his shuffle and picks up a single wide of mid on
fine shot, this was pitched up just enough for Warner to push it very solidly past mid off's dive
punched from the crease to covers
right up around the blockhole at 141 kph, Warner is off balance as he digs it out
good length coming in a tad around off, worked with a closed face behind square on leg as Smith moves across immediately
turned gently between midwicket and mid on off the pad for a single
walks outside off stump and easily plays out an incoming back of a length ball to mid on
had him in some trouble this time as he took a long stride across and outside off, managed a thick inside edge square on the leg side
closes the face and whips a length delivery in front of mid on for a sharp single
short of a good length, absolutely no room, blocked down the track
quite overpitched, and Smith easily sends this racing between bowler and the non-striker with a firm drive
comes across and turns this incoming length ball to midwicket
off and middle line, Smith likes it there and has the space with his shuffle to time it past midwicket, trickles into the boundary
good length, some way outside off, no angle to work with, so Smith leaves
could have been more runs had Smith connected on this short of a length ball headed just over leg stump
uh oh, this has jumped from a good length, Warner was half forward looking to punch on the up and he had no time or room to adjust, only manages to awkwardly pop a dolly to point
plays out a good length ball around off, down the pitch
left alone outside off stump
right on off stump line, good length, played back from the crease
that gets big on Bailey as Anderson digs it in, but the captain also does well to swerve inside the line
defended safely down the track to the bowler
overpitched once more from Woakes, and Smith os right behind it with his shuffle, and a high followthrough earns him four more through mid off
short of a length, outside off, he gets on his toes and defends
England are interested as Smith shuffles into this length ball as he decides to let it go, hit him on the flap, but that was always missing off
uses the bat this time and leans well forward, getting low to defend this length ball
good length ball, just outside off, defended
too full once more, and slight angle in to Smith, that is all he needs, as he whips through midwicket, there is a man out there in the deep
pushed towards extra cover
that was moving in full and late, but some way outside off, he reaches forward and pushes solidly to mid off
good length outside off, some away shape as it nears the keeper after batsman shoulders arms
short ball now, around the neck, Bailey swivels but cannot pull it past square leg
opens the face as he leans to defend this good length ball around off
takes a stride forward and softly plays out a fuller one to covers
bowls it too full first up and Smith goes too hard at it, can't find the timing, and hits it hard into the pitch, Broad puts a hand out in his followthrough
he is in such good form, he can stand and punch a length ball without any problem, away to cover
turned it behind square leg for a couple
walks just outside off and keeps bat close to the body to let this length ball pass
that shuffle working nicely for Smith, takes this length ball from outside off and goes through square leg again
takes a step forward and lifts bat high to let a rising length ball go
walks a long way outside off stump and lets another length ball rush past
short and wide but Smith cannot find timing as he tries the cut, the ball rolls to point
moves across, gets on top of the bounce and punches to covers
widish length ball, Smith has a look and allows it to go through to the keeper
lots of width again, Smith does not attack it, and he cannot place his push as well, finds point
overpitched, he gets it through the covers this time, but there is a sweeper in too
they're keeping it wide outside off to Smith, he punches off the back foot wide of third man now
carefully pats away this angled good length ball towards midwicket
just back of a length, no room, Bailey forces it to the off side
pitched up outside off stump, Bailey flags it through
gets going off the 16th ball as he cuts to the right of third man, wasn't too short, but he had the width

and he's gone next ball, that short leg coming into play for Broad, who bangs it in short, Bailey is hopping and fending in hope, eyes off the ball, no that it has bounced too much, but he is completely taken by surprise, and short leg is in the right place at the right time
very full outside off first up at 131 kph, he forces a drive to mid off
good length, tight line just outside off, defended
back of a length, punched off the back foot to covers
length ball played out watchfully to mid on
overpitched on off stump line, and Smith is ready with a forcing whip to deep midwicket
left alone outside off stump
nice carry through to the keeper as batsman moves across and lets this length ball be
drags it wider outside off, enough to be called
takes this from a long way outside off and taps it front of midwicket
solidly forward and defends this length ball to covers
shortish, not that much lift, Maxwell swivels and drags a pull behind square
pitched slightly fuller, moving away a tad, testing the marker again, but not wide enough this time
Smith is in his own world, Broad pitches it too full, just outside off, Smith sends it into the deep midwicket rope with a powerful whip
fullish ball driven back to the bowler
back of a length, no room at all, defended to extra cover
loses his shape as he tries to smash it through the covers, mistimes to point
nicely on to the front foot this time to defend to covers
short of a good length, he gets behind and on top of the bounce to block
stays on the crease and beside the line to guide this short of a length ball to third man
short of a good length, some angle into the right hander, who knocks it well in front of the man at short leg
bouncer, 136 kph, just outside off, he bends inside the line and tries to steer it over the keeper, but misses
angled in around off stump, good length, pushed away to point
goes back and across to a good length ball on off and defends carefully
forces a good length ball from the crease this time, cannot beat cover
tries to drive a length ball on the up as he moves forward but cannot time it
good length ball outside off stump, guided behind square
back of a length around off stump, worked square on the leg side
nudged on the leg side close to the pitch for another single, this shortish ball came in and had him in some trouble
walks across and clips it, in the air for a while, but safely short of the man at square leg
moves across, keeps bat close to body, opens the face and defends to cover
walks down this time and meets the length ball with purpose, but mid on is in the way
a low full toss outside off to start, Maxwell hits it to long on, got it off the toe end
down the track to work it with the turn to long on
on a length now, he moves forward and across and nudges to midwicket

has Buttler recovered in time to make the stumping? Smith walked out looking to work it to the leg side, missed, but it also popped out of Buttler's gloves, the keeper picked it up on the bounce, Smith seemed to think it was a lost cause trying to make his ground, then saw some hope, but it was too late to ground his bat in, out by some inches as Buttler broke the stumps, yet again, Moeen Ali produces a massive wicket
comes forward to defend a tossed up ball to covers
some counter from Maxwell, FInch overpitches, also offers width, and Maxwell clobbers it on the up between extra cover and mid off
works a length ball from middle to mid on
on the line of the stumps again, defended to the bowler
whips it in the air, but it is wide of mid on and four more, used the angle into him to whip that off the pad
gets on his toes to a shortish ball and punches nicely, point dives to save a few
pushed at a length delivery on the up again, checked the stroke in the end, and it falls well short of mid off
pitched up, just outside off, eased down to long on
turning in from outside off, worked to midwicket
comes forward to defend down the track
shortish ball, he stays back, waits for it to come on, and turns it on front of square
uses the turn in to him to work it behind square
short ball not rising a lot, he controls it along the ground behind square as he swivels, fine leg cuts it off
Maxwell looking good with a solid back foot punch to mid off
shot! Finn overpitches and what a response from Maxwell, driving on the up again, right between bowler and mid off, that flew away
short of a length now, he is behind the line to block
into the pad now from Finn and Maxwell tickles it just past the keeper's dive
eagerly attacks a widish ball but cannot time the cut
pitches it up around off, is pushed to short mid on
takes a long stride forward outside off to defend
driven down to long off for a single
fullish ball, he reaches for it and eases it to long on
length ball played with the turn to short mid on
bat in front of pad as he defends to the bowler
full and wide, Maxwell goes for it, there is no slip, and it beats Ali's dive at the fine third man boundary
he is drilling them now, mid on has to scramble to his right to stop this one
opens the face on a good length ball to run it to point
thick edge down to third man off this length ball as Maxwell pushes with an open face again
short of a good length, he moves across and defends solidly
overpitched, he drives but cannot beat mid off to his left, a slide saves some runs
works it with the spin in front of square leg
goes back and punches this length delivery against the turn through the covers, that is timed well enough to beat the chasing fielder to the rope
length ball into the pads, turned to square leg
overpitched on off stump, hit to long on
hit to short mid on now
bounced a touch more than he thought it would as he came forward to defend
flows forward to check his drive with an open face to point
Ali won't get there from third man, Maxwell has carved this length delivery behind point, it was uppish, but wide of the man
another nice looking drive, picks out extra cover now
already forward to meet this length ball when it comes off the pitch, takes the single to the sweeper
held the line after pitching good length just outside off, Marsh stayed half forward and tapped it square
opens the face late on this length delivery as he moves forward, gets a single to third man, Maxwell is looking really good
fullish delivery around off, patted down to long on
comes down the track, takes it on the full, and hits it on the bounce to short mid on
too full, he hits it hard past the bowler's dive to long off
spinning in towards off stump, nudged in the direction of midwicket
full on middle and leg, turned in front of square, deep midwicket runs in quickly to keep them to one
pushed off the back foot to midwicket
gets right on top of the bounce to punch a short of a length ball to extra cover
tight line on off stump, he makes an effort to get the bat in front of the pad and just keeps it out
back of a length, turned behind square on the leg side, and Maxwell comes back for the second
nice delivery, holding the line after being angled in shortish on the line of the stumps, handled well too, as he stays inside the line and runs it behind point
Bopara with a fine stop at extra cover off this push
tries to take a single as he guides a short of a length ball behind square but cannot get it past point
punches a good length ball to short mid on
pushed off the front foot towards point
drives a tossed up ball to long off
well forward and opens the face on a length delivery to squeeze it to point
played off the pad with the turn to square leg, man runs in from the deep and prevents the second
that came in from short of a length and hit him high, on the thigh pad
tries to whip this short of a length but misses and is hit on the thigh pad again
opens the face and carves this widish ball to the right of third man
back of a length, angled in, worked off the pad to midwicket
into the pad again, from a good length, turned to fine leg
short of a length, outside off, tapped to covers
stinging reverse sweep as he connects on the full, backward point somehow stops it with a dive to his left
Maxwell goes to fifty with a much finer, reverse paddle this time, that is also 1000 ODI runs for him
played out to midwicket
tries the reverse paddle again, ends up hitting it too high, but it falls in vacant space way behind the keeper
pushed off the back foot to midwicket
rides the bounce on a short of a length ball and guides it to third man
comes forward and defends a good length ball to point
on middle stump line, he shuffles and works it to long leg
on middle stump line, good length, he defends off the back foot
pitched fuller and around off stump now, he gathers himself in time and brings a straight defensive bat down on it
that has come in and bounced too, catching Maxwell in an awkward position, England appeal for caught behind is turned down though
keeps the length shortish as Marsh comes out, he can only tap it back to the bowler
turned straight to midwicket now
pushes forward and gets it off the inside part of the bat, past the bowler
pushes a pitched up ball with the turn to midwicket
fuller and quicker as Maxwell comes out, cannot get under the ball and pushes it to long on
tossed up and coming down around the blockhole, dug out to covers, that is another tight over of offspin
Ponting style, one hand off the bat, forcing push carving a length ball to third man
that is a dismissive pull to the deep midwicket boundary as Marsh fetches this short ball, not much bounce there
nudges this short of a length ball square on the leg side
almost chopped on, wanted to guide this short of a length ball to third man, it moved in to cramp him for room
he's tried to drive that on the up, inside edged it on to pad, and it has missed the stumps again, not by much
reverse sweep again from Maxwell as this sits up outside off, and beats backward point's dive
fuller ball but Maxwell has another go at the reverse sweep, finds backward point this time
now scoops it from just outside off stump, fine on the leg side
turned to midwicket
goes for a huge sweep, does not quite connect, it goes down to long leg
spinning in to leg stump, they take the single in front of square
short ball pulled to deep midwicket
good length ball slanted in, he uses that to work it in front of square
cramped him as it came back from just short of a length, he plays it to midwicket
this full one moved in a tad, late too, which is why he could not place the drive too well, and mid on cut it off
full but too much angle into the pads and Marsh whips it away easily, just over midwicket's jump
another pull, but this time deep square leg is able to run around and stop it
around middle and leg, played square
overpitched ball forced straight to mid on, missed out there
that is onto the grass bank beyond deep square leg, what a pick up this is, short ball, he is on the front foot and just lifts it cleanly
shortish and wide, comes a touch slowly off the pitch, and he checks his push to point
123 kph length delivery this time, he takes a big step out to push to extra cover
flows into a straight push now, straight to the bowler too
goes for four first ball, length ball into the pad, and Maxwell uses the angle to flick it to fine leg
now he charges down the track and swings at a length ball, it stays in the air for a long while, and falls just inside the rope at deep midwicket
forces a pull off a slower short ball, and it loops to deep midwicket, falling well short

has that carried to short extra cover, Maxwell checked his push as he came forward but could not stop the ball from ballooning, Bopara just managed to get his fingers to it as he dived to his left, will go as a drop that, but Bopara has created that chance with his quick reaction
wow, he tries a big reverse hit against Anderson now, but this is a slower length ball, and he is beaten
thickish inside edge as he pushes at this incoming good length ball, midwicket stops it
slower length ball, he defends it from close to the splice
short ball, coming in, he swings it down in to the ground, to long leg
makes plenty of room to a 110 kph length ball from the back of the hand and clobbers it between extra cover and mid off
leaves the crease this time and also makes some room, but it beaten as this length ball bounces
a yorker arrives, right on the stumps, Maxwell brings the bat down in time
punches this length ball down the ground, past mid off, but long on slides across to stop it
turned to deep midwicket for a single
opens up and moves across, setting himself up for the swing to the leg side, but cannot get hold of this low full toss, which goes between his legs, just past leg stump
slower and fullish, angled in as well, forced down to long on
slow bouncer, Maxwell backed away and gave it everything, could not connect though
phew, that has been drilled way over extra cover, that was almost a yorker outside off, but not only was Maxwell able to dig it out, he also got incredible elevation
slower one down the pad, tickled square on the leg side
backs away, comes down the track and has a swing, beaten by the bounce
137 kph length ball smashed straight at the non-striker, who goes down just in time, mid on has little chance of stopping that
full, angled in, just down the leg side as he shuffles across and misses the nudge
four more, Maxwell goes leg side again, takes a low full toss from outside leg stump and cracks it over mid off
ridiculous, he's standing legs wide apart to this slower one and reverse hit it high over short third man, one bounce over the rope
this is a boundary flood, Maxwell sends this widish length delivery crashing into the deep cover boundary with a savage swing of the bat
stand and deliver stuff from the other end now, Mitch Marsh has sent this overpitched ball smack into the wide long off boundary, it was right in the slot
swing and a miss to this good length ball now
slower bouncer, 124 kph, Marsh swings and misses once more
that is incredible speed off the bat as Marsh powerfully strikes an overpitched ball straight down the ground
Broad with the yorker just outside off, Marsh squeezes it to long off for one

oh dear, whatever the format, he seems to have a thing for the 90s, backs away to leg and swings at a short ball, the top edge is taken safely by the keeper as he moves a few steps to his left, 95 off 98 on this pitch, take a bow Glenn Maxwell
length ball turning in from outside off, pushed to long on
leans into a drive and gets off the mark with a single to long off
taps it down the track, bowler half-stops it with a dive
finds the bowler with a straight push
tossed up full, Marsh moves to fifty at his home ground with a whip to long on
has a go at the pull but this does not quite come on and he is hit on the thigh pad
driven straight and down to long off
back of a length, dabbed to backward point
Marsh pulls another one to the deep midwicket boundary, this got a touch big on him but he managed to place it alright
short and wide now from Broad, Marsh stands on the crease and thumps it through extra cover, well wide of the sweeper
into the pad, fine leg is up, Broad is fortunate Marsh nudges it straight to the man
was backing away to leg, Broad follows him, and Haddin gets a single with an awkward inside edge to fine leg

gone trying to sneak in the second, and it is the big wicket of Marsh, Haddin guided this shortish ball to third man, Anderson is there, they try to take him on for the second, not a wise decision, the throw is fired straight at the keeper, who scores a direct hit at the non-striker's, catching Marsh way short
cramped for room as he tries to push this off the back foot
mistimes the back foot punch to point, lots of bounce there
no room again as this arrives just back of a length on off, tapped on to the pitch
on middle stump line from a good length, patted back to the bowler, suddenly the momentum has disappeared
Haddin regains some of that with a ripping straight drive between the bowler and mid off, was overpitched from the bowler but that was some superb timing
tight start to the over with a good length ball on off, squeezed out to short extra
full and angled in to middle, pushed down the ground
tries to make room on the leg side but the full delivery follows him and he can only push it for a single
pitched up delivery pushed to midwicket
a single to the sweeper is all they get this time

and after that run out, Haddin has slapped this straight and loopy to midwicket on the edge of the circle, wanted to pull, had to really drag it as it came off slowly and bounced, ends up as a simple catch
good length ball on the stumps tapped to a diving midwicket
to midwicket's right this time, and only a single is given away off another tight length ball
comes in off a good length, Johnson leaves
moving in once again, close enough for Johnson to play, and push to point
this goes the other way now, terrific bowling, after a couple that came in, this holds the line against the incoming angle, beating him by a long way
an understandably careful Johnson defends a good length delivery around off
Faulkner charges out, but Broad follows him with an angled ball and Faulkner's awkward heave cannot connect
full, outside off, Faulkner is backing away at the start, but he gets to it in the end, hammering it through extra cover
short of a length into the body, nudged to leg for a single
Johnson is getting some rippers out there, Broad gets it to straighten against considerable angle from round the stumps, and Johnson is left feeling for it
gets bat on ball to this length ball and collects his first run, towards mid off
slower length ball just outside off, Faulkner waits and taps it to the sweeper
starts the over with a sweep, this is a length delivery headed into the pad, and Faulkner gets down on his knee to send it soaring to the left of fine leg
slower and fuller, he squeezes it straight down the ground for two
short and slow, sitting up, Faulkner sets himself up and swings it flat between deep midwicket and deep square leg, bounces just inside
proper bouncer now, Faulkner down on his knees to avoid that, good reaction with the urge to hit everything at this stage
has a heave and misses this yorker into the legs, the ball falls down on to the crease, and a single is stolen
Johnson wants to paddle this length ball fine with the angle, manages a weak leading edge that falls down well short of the bowler
swings hard at a low full toss outside off, drags it to long on
makes some room outside leg and swings a length ball out to deep midwicket, didnt get hold of that too well
Faulkner winds up and slams another bouncer, and this goes all the way, over the jumping fielder at deep midwicket
more runs, a thick outside edge as he goes for a pitched up ball outside off, and it flies past the keeper's jump
helpful full toss, Faulkner uses the angle in to him and mows it way over deep midwicket, on to the grass banks
six more, what an over for Australia, this is short, Faulkner has backed away and played some sort of a flat forehand, on one leg too, and the ball has cleared the man at long on
mishits this length ball in the air, and well short of long off
has a go at the pull off this lifter, but mishits it tamely to the off side instead
Johnson departs, backs away and swings hard, the length ball soars way up and comes down at extra cover
Faulkner keeps thumping pull after pull as England keep bouncing him, long on runs around to his right
short once again, too short, says square leg umpire, even as Faulkner swings and misses, harsh call that
back of a length, Faulkner cannot connect as he eyes deep midwicket once more

Faulkner has zoomed to 50 off 24 balls as he smacks this short of a length ball out of sight, into the grass bank over deep midwicket, was expecting something like this and had set himself up, that was right off the middle of the bat

inn2.comm: gets it to straighten on the left-hander, just back of a length, Moeen defends off the back foot
a touch outside off this time, similar short of a good length, Moeen sends it down to third man
good length ball allowed to go past with the angle outside off
gets forward and drives an overpitched ball but it swings in and he finds mid off
does not get the front foot, deals with the inswing nicely as he squeezes a full delivery through the covers, lovely timing
overpitched again, outside off, Bell attacks it and cracks it past a diving cover
swings in full in to the left hander, turned to midwicket
pitches just outside off on a good length and bounces through to the keeper as Moeen leaves
good length ball on off stump line, played out solidly
drives on the fuller length now and through the gap at cover, it needs a slide near the boundary to be reined in
good length ball angled in around off, played down the track towards the leg side
left alone outside off stump
heads down the leg side from a good length
holds the line around off stump, just back of a length, defended
angled in towards the pads on a fuller length and Moeen flicks it behind square, too quick for fine leg to get there in time
flashes at a short of a length wide one, and is beaten
full length again, Moeen drives nicely but short extra slides to his left to stop it
bouncer, headed just down the leg side even as Moeen ducks, that has bounced way too much
tries to launch into this widish length ball but it is not easy to smash deliveries on the up on this pitch and Moeen is beaten
inswinging yorker arrives on off stump, Moeen jams it out
short of a good length ball defended to the off side
back of a length, coming in a tad, played out solidly

super reaction from Haddin after a peach from Hazlewood, hits the track short of a length, just about holds the line, bang on the line of the stumps too, Bell has to play, and Haddin sticks out a hand as he falls to his right to pouch it
moves forward outside off stump to defend a good length ball
pitches it up around off stump, Taylor gets a defensive bat down in time, Hazlewood feels the need to throw the ball back at the batsman
stands on the crease and hits this length ball on the up to mid off
didn't seem to have timed it too well initially, came off the inner part of the bat, but Bailey is beaten by a long way to the deep square leg rope
has a flash and a miss outside off again as this zooms from short of a length
pitched up, into the pads again and Moeen forces a whip through midwicket, easy put away
bouncer, Moeen ducks under it immediately
good length, around off stump, he plays from the crease towards extra cover
walks across and tries to hook a 137 kph bouncer, misses
pushes a length delivery to the off side
turns  a pitched up delivery straight to midwicket with a closed face
good length, around middle, he shuffles and plays it out to mid on
bat closes in his hands again and square leg stops this incoming length delivery with a dive
starts full and into the pad, Moeen flicks it in the air down to long leg
jerks across in the crease and taps a short of a length ball to midwicket
good length ball into the pads, sent down to long leg
moves across, has a look at a bouncing length ball and lets it go
shot, Johnson has kept pitching it up this over, and this time Moeen goes for a drive on the up, and nails the gap between extra cover and mid off
short of a length this time, defended tightly from the crease, bat close to the body
jumps down the track and drags it past square leg, he is in the air as he plays the shot
moves across and tries to work it square, but the short of a length ball hits him and falls on to the crease
pitched up, he is more comfortable with that length as he thumps a drive to mid off
cuts this short of a length ball straight  to backward point, wasn't too wide
walks forward and defends a length ball to the off side
pulled down to deep backward square leg

Johnson strikes, via a sharp take from Maxwell, Taylor reaches for the drive at a good length delivery leaving him on the angle, he can't keep it down, Maxwell goes down on his left and stretches to take it low at backward point, they check for the no ball, it is tight, but it is settled in favour of the bowler
welcomed by a sharp lifter which he fends down behind point
stands tall and pushes on the up to extra cover
good length, right on off, he walks across and plays it to mid on
decides to stay on the crease to a pitched up ball holding its line outside off, guides it to point
Moeen picks up four more with a flash of the wrists as he sends this length delivery on the up through the covers
plays out a length ball to point from the crease
short of a length, angled in, tapped to midwicket
arches back and cuts it late, down to third man
opens the face and runs this length delivery down to third man
on top of the bounce as leans back and controls the pull past midwicket, enough on it to roll into the rope
fine drive off a fullish one, but extra cover runs across and dives to his right to stop it
length ball pushed from the crease to covers
bouncer dug in around leg stump line, he ducks

and out of nowhere, he comes up with a snorter on target, Moeen can only fend this to wide slip, short ball, climbing steeply on off, Moeen can't avoid that, tries to ride the bounce and survive, fails

Johnson all over England, yet again, captain has left his first ball which has crashed into off stump, good length delivery, holds the line, Morgan makes a late decision to let it go, and pays for it instantly
that wasn't far from off stump, but it was the right hander and he can leave it on the angle to prevent the hat-trick
143 kph short of a length ball carries just down the leg side, not called a wide, could have taken a bit of clothing or pad on its way to Haddin
angles it too much, down the leg side
hits the pad this time from a good length, there is a shout but that is headed down easily
eases a pitched up ball straight to mid off
turned off the pad to deep square leg
full and moving in to the pads again, flicked to fine leg
back of a length, coming in a tad, defended from the crease
